author: Brian
title: WWE Elimination Chamber: Start time and full match card
text:
Feb 12, 2017 at 11:04a ET 0Shares 
Three titles could change hands Sunday night at the SmackDown-exclusive Elimination Chamber pay-per-view, and John Cena will have to beat five other men if he hopes to enter WrestleMania 33 as the WWE World Champion. 
WWE Elimination Chamber will begin at 8:00 p.m. ET on the WWE Network . The kickoff show, which includes one match, will start at 7:00 p.m. ET. 
Here's the full match card for Sunday's show. Via WWE.com Kickoff show: Mojo Rawley vs. Curt Hawkins 
Via WWE.com Kalisto and Apollo Crews vs. Dolph Ziggler in a handicap match 
Via WWE.com Nikki Bella vs. Natalya 
Via WWE.com The Ascension vs. Rhyno and Heath Slater vs. The Usos vs. American Alpha vs. Breezango vs. The Vaudevillains in a tag team turmoil match for the SmackDown Tag Team Championship 
What is a tag team turmoil match? It's somewhat similar to the Elimination Chamber format. Two of the six teams start in the ring, and the other four remain in each of the corners. When one team is eliminated, another steps in to take their place. Via WWE.com Becky Lynch vs. Mickie James 
Via WWE.com Luke Harper vs. Randy Orton 
Via WWE.com Alexa Bliss vs. Naomi for the SmackDown Women's Championship 
Via WWE.com John Cena vs. Dean Ambrose vs. Baron Corbin vs. AJ Styles vs. The Miz vs. Bray Wyatt in an Elimination Chamber match for the WWE World Championship 
In the Elimination Chamber, two men start the match in the ring, while the other four are locked away in their own chamber. After a certain amount of time, one of the pods will open at random. The last man standing wins. Via WWE.com
